poland and the outer .
in the meeting of ministers of the countries of the agency space european held the last week accepted to poland as twelfth member of the esa . is the second country member of the esa the former bloc of europe the this , after of the republic czech , became in full member the 12 of november of 2008 ) .
poland set a intensive cooperation with the esa in the year 1994 and for the subsequent years took in the commission of projects of the agency .
however , the way of poland to the outer began much before .
the enthusiasts poles already fished to the flights the space before of the second war world , although not always had their work .
remember , example , the conference of a. šternfeld in the astronomic centre of warsaw in the , the 6 of december of 1933 , presented their ideas on the study nevertheless &quot; introduction to the cosmonautics &quot; .
the ideas the young engineering newborn ( the 1905 ) was to the indifferent assistants and , years after , šternfeld had that the dr. jan gadomski had been the only had shown interest in their work .
in the year 1934 šternfeld was in france the prize robert esnault-pelterie and andré louis moralist their &quot; introduction to the cosmonautics &quot; .
the doctor jan gadomski ( 1899 - 1966 ) , mentioned previously , became more later in a great drive of the astronomy and of the cosmonautics .
published hundreds of articles in polish journals and wrote a series of books dedicated to this scientific discipline .
gadomski became in a promoter of the cosmonautics , was known in all the world and their contribution to the science was rewarded when their name to one of the cráteres of the hidden face of the moon .
already in the year 1925 was in poland a dresina was to be provista of a engine of rockets .
unfortunately , is who was the author of the proposal and not know the destalles the project .
not is clear if the rocket was to be used to the testing of the dresina or to their quiet .
the information on this dresina limited to the collection in the press of the time .
to from the year 1933 the polish artillery began to deal to the rockets .
the research was funded the komórka techniki uzbrojenia in cooperation with the prof . mieczyslawem wolfkem and prof . gustawem mokrzyckiegim .
to from the material retained , ago clear that the research came the crowd of the practical evidence .
not however , with the arrival of the german troops , was the research .
in the year 1937 am in the press was the example of a missile of fotoeléctrico hunting designed the engineering rohoziński and the next year was published the study &quot; rakieta - powietrzna rakietobomba lotnicza torpeda &quot; , the author leliwa-krzywoblocki .
both projects were for the military use of the engines to rockets .
little before of the war , the committee she scientific provisional ( tymczasowy komitet doradczo-naukowy responsible ) of all the projects of techniques of rockets to military use and coordinaba all the jobs .
the committee was founded in 1937 , but after of two years of activity , was cut the start of the war .
other studies dedicated to the cosmonautics appeared in the polish press after of the war thanks the work of the society igor of astronáutica ( polskie towarzystwo astronautyczne ) .
in the edition of november of 1954 of the magazine problemy ago first reference time to the society with four articles very dedicated to the astronáutica .
in one of them , the prof . m. subotowicze , proposed the creation of a society devoted to the cosmonautics .
in time already had put in projects of artificial satellite and was obvious that the cosmic research was a discipline with prospects of future .
since principles of 1956 the society igor of astronáutica ( pta ) hoped to be part of the international federation of astronáutica ( up in 1951 ) and in autumn of that same year the pta became in full member .
the next year the first president of the pta , kazimierz zarankiewicz ( 1902 - 1959 ) , happened to be the of of the international federation of astronáutica .
occupy this office to their death in 1959 .
to from the 1956 , the pta took of significant way in the development the sonda rocket rm ( rakieta meteorologiczna ) , was a success and became in the first polish rocket in the was to out scientific research .
the first kind rm-1 was completed in 1957 and launched first time the 10 of october of 1958 .
the rocket had a back of 1.800 metres , a 80 cm of length and not receive to the 5 kg of weight .
more later , completed of build the version rm-1a and in summer of 1959 were the evidence airlines of the rockets rm-2 of two stages in the desert of błędów .
the rocket severs 1,4 metres and pesaba a 11,5 kg.
another kind of rocket in development was to be subject of scientific real study . the rocket rm-34 was to have a back of 14,5 km and their mission would control the wind of level .
however , in 1962 were the jobs .
the successor of the first rockets the kind rm was the rocket meteor-1 , was for the years 1962 and 1965 .
diseñó as rocket of two stages , with a total length of 510 cm and a initial weight of 32,5 kg.
proceeded three ( types called meteor-1a , -1b and -1c ) , differed between itself the available space to the scientific equipment .
in the rocket meteor-1a the available space to the volume was of 0,4 litres , in the meteor-1b of 0,34 litres and in the meteor-1c of 0,62 litres .
the fundamental back in the three types was of 37 km.
between the years 1965 and 1968 developed in the institute appraisal the rocket meteor-2 , whose first evidence airlines were in october of 1970 .
the rocket meteor-2 had a initial weight of 380 kg and was capable of to a useful weight of 10 kg to 60 km of level .
subsequently was the version meteor-2h and meteor-3 .
